# Core scientific stack
numpy
pillow
pyyaml
matplotlib

# Computer vision
# Use opencv-python-headless instead on servers without GUI/X libs.
opencv-python

# Deep learning
# NOTE: On Linux/CUDA targets you will likely want a CUDA-specific build of
# torch/torchvision pulled from the PyTorch index URL. See
# docs/LINUX_WHEELHOUSE_BUILD.md.
torch
torchvision

# Detection / segmentation helpers (Roboflow)
supervision

# RF-DETR — Roboflow publishes `rfdetr` on PyPI.
# If the wheel is not resolvable on the target Python/Linux/CUDA combo, vendor
# the wheel or source manually. See docs/MODEL_WEIGHTS.md.
rfdetr

# SAM (Segment Anything) — Meta's `segment-anything` is distributed via GitHub
# source, not as an official PyPI package. Intentionally NOT listed here.
# If you need SAM, install from a vendored source archive or vendored wheel.
# See docs/MODEL_WEIGHTS.md.
# segment-anything
